{
    "publish_date": "2013-01-17T16:02:14.000Z", 
    "score": 0.00013425468904244817, 
    "video_length": "PT4M24S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "You look down and see a yellow pencil lying on your desk.", 
            "dur": "3.482", 
            "start": "14.603"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Your eyes, and then your brain, are collecting", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "18.085"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "all sorts of information about the pencil:", 
            "dur": "2.615", 
            "start": "20.385"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "its size,", 
            "dur": "0.566", 
            "start": "23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "color,", 
            "dur": "0.524", 
            "start": "23.566"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "shape,", 
            "dur": "0.43", 
            "start": "24.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "distance,", 
            "dur": "0.752", 
            "start": "24.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and more.", 
            "dur": "1.403", 
            "start": "25.272"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, how exactly does this happen?", 
            "dur": "2.215", 
            "start": "26.675"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The ancient Greeks were the first", 
            "dur": "1.154", 
            "start": "28.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to think more or less scientifically", 
            "dur": "1.714", 
            "start": "30.044"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "about what light is and how vision works.", 
            "dur": "2.643", 
            "start": "31.758"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Some Greek philosophers,", 
            "dur": "0.883", 
            "start": "34.401"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "including Plato and Pythagoras,", 
            "dur": "2.144", 
            "start": "35.284"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "thought that light originated in our eyes", 
            "dur": "1.906", 
            "start": "37.428"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and that vision happened when little, invisible probes", 
            "dur": "2.602", 
            "start": "39.334"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "were sent to gather information about far-away objects.", 
            "dur": "2.912", 
            "start": "41.936"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It took over a thousand years", 
            "dur": "1.334", 
            "start": "44.848"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "before the Arab scientist, Alhazen,", 
            "dur": "2.223", 
            "start": "46.182"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "figured out that the old, Greek theory of light couldn&#39;t be right.", 
            "dur": "3.714", 
            "start": "48.405"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In Alhazen&#39;s picture, your eyes don&#39;t send out", 
            "dur": "2.804", 
            "start": "52.119"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "invisible, intelligence-gathering probes,", 
            "dur": "2.089", 
            "start": "54.923"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they simply collect the light that falls into them.", 
            "dur": "3.164", 
            "start": "57.012"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Alhazen&#39;s theory accounts for a fact", 
            "dur": "2.145", 
            "start": "60.176"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that the Greek&#39;s couldn&#39;t easily explain:", 
            "dur": "2.245", 
            "start": "62.321"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "why it gets dark sometimes.", 
            "dur": "2.327", 
            "start": "64.566"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The idea is that very few objects actually emit their own light.", 
            "dur": "3.902", 
            "start": "66.893"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The special, light-emitting objects,", 
            "dur": "2.314", 
            "start": "70.795"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like the sun", 
            "dur": "0.982", 
            "start": "73.109"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or a lightbulb,", 
            "dur": "0.846", 
            "start": "74.091"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are known as sources of light.", 
            "dur": "2.569", 
            "start": "74.937"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Most of the things we see,", 
            "dur": "1.218", 
            "start": "77.506"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like that pencil on your desk,", 
            "dur": "1.606", 
            "start": "78.724"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are simply reflecting light from a source", 
            "dur": "2.565", 
            "start": "80.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "rather than producing their own.", 
            "dur": "1.875", 
            "start": "82.895"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, when you look at your pencil,", 
            "dur": "2.015", 
            "start": "84.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the light that hits your eye actually originated at the sun", 
            "dur": "2.825", 
            "start": "86.785"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and has traveled millions of miles across empty space", 
            "dur": "2.979", 
            "start": "89.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "before bouncing off the pencil and into your eye,", 
            "dur": "2.815", 
            "start": "92.589"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is pretty cool when you think about it.", 
            "dur": "2.212", 
            "start": "95.404"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, what exactly is the stuff that is emitted from the sun", 
            "dur": "2.797", 
            "start": "97.616"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and how do we see it?", 
            "dur": "1.721", 
            "start": "100.413"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Is it a particle, like atoms,", 
            "dur": "1.751", 
            "start": "102.134"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or is it a wave, like ripples on the surface of a pond?", 
            "dur": "3.633", 
            "start": "103.885"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Scientists in the modern era would spend a couple of hundred years", 
            "dur": "2.859", 
            "start": "107.518"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "figuring out the answer to this question.", 
            "dur": "2.281", 
            "start": "110.377"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Isaac Newton was one of the earliest.", 
            "dur": "1.771", 
            "start": "112.658"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Newton believed that light is made up", 
            "dur": "1.757", 
            "start": "114.429"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of tiny, atom-like particles, which he called corpuscles.", 
            "dur": "3.922", 
            "start": "116.186"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Using this assumption, he was able to explain some properties of light.", 
            "dur": "3.876", 
            "start": "120.108"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For example, refraction,", 
            "dur": "1.394", 
            "start": "123.984"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is how a beam of light appears to bend", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "125.378"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as it passes from air into water.", 
            "dur": "2.006", 
            "start": "127.738"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, in science, even geniuses sometimes get things wrong.", 
            "dur": "4.121", 
            "start": "129.744"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the 19th century, long after Newton died,", 
            "dur": "2.818", 
            "start": "133.865"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "scientists did a series of experiments", 
            "dur": "2.105", 
            "start": "136.683"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that clearly showed that light can&#39;t be made up", 
            "dur": "2.584", 
            "start": "138.788"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of tiny, atom-like particles.", 
            "dur": "2.593", 
            "start": "141.372"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For one thing, two beams of light that cross paths", 
            "dur": "2.935", 
            "start": "143.965"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "don&#39;t interact with each other at all.", 
            "dur": "2.444", 
            "start": "146.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If light were made of tiny, solid balls,", 
            "dur": "2.367", 
            "start": "149.344"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "then you would expect that some of the particles from Beam A", 
            "dur": "2.931", 
            "start": "151.711"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would crash into some of the particles from Beam B.", 
            "dur": "2.743", 
            "start": "154.642"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If that happened, the two particles involved in the collision", 
            "dur": "2.494", 
            "start": "157.385"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would bounce off in random directions.", 
            "dur": "2.331", 
            "start": "159.879"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, that doesn&#39;t happen.", 
            "dur": "1.477", 
            "start": "162.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The beams of light pass right through each other", 
            "dur": "1.94", 
            "start": "163.687"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as you can check for yourself", 
            "dur": "1.05", 
            "start": "165.627"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with two laser pointers and some chalk dust.", 
            "dur": "2.262", 
            "start": "166.677"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For another thing, light makes interference patterns.", 
            "dur": "2.505", 
            "start": "168.939"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Interference patterns are the complicated undulations that happen", 
            "dur": "3.502", 
            "start": "171.444"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when two wave patterns occupy the same space.", 
            "dur": "3.035", 
            "start": "174.946"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They can be seen when two objects", 
            "dur": "1.55", 
            "start": "177.981"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "disturb the surface of a still pond,", 
            "dur": "2.224", 
            "start": "179.531"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and also when two point-like sources of light", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "181.755"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are placed near each other.", 
            "dur": "2.189", 
            "start": "184.205"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Only waves make interference patterns,", 
            "dur": "1.742", 
            "start": "186.394"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "particles don&#39;t.", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "188.136"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And, as a bonus, understanding that light acts like a wave", 
            "dur": "3.356", 
            "start": "189.636"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "leads naturally to an explanation of what color is", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "192.992"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and why that pencil looks yellow.", 
            "dur": "1.703", 
            "start": "195.992"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, it&#39;s settled then, light is a wave, right?", 
            "dur": "3.341", 
            "start": "197.695"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Not so fast!", 
            "dur": "1.651", 
            "start": "201.036"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the 20th century, scientists did experiments", 
            "dur": "2.691", 
            "start": "202.687"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that appear to show light acting like a particle.", 
            "dur": "3.054", 
            "start": "205.378"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For instance, when you shine light on a metal,", 
            "dur": "2.712", 
            "start": "208.432"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the light transfers its energy to the atoms in the metal", 
            "dur": "3.258", 
            "start": "211.144"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in discrete packets called quanta.", 
            "dur": "2.697", 
            "start": "214.402"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, we can&#39;t just forget about properties like interference, either.", 
            "dur": "3.702", 
            "start": "217.099"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So these quanta of light aren&#39;t at all like", 
            "dur": "2.365", 
            "start": "220.801"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the tiny, hard spheres Newton imagined.", 
            "dur": "2.833", 
            "start": "223.166"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This result, that light sometimes behaves like a particle", 
            "dur": "2.753", 
            "start": "225.999"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and sometimes behaves like a wave,", 
            "dur": "2.39", 
            "start": "228.752"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "led to a revolutionary new physics theory called", 
            "dur": "2.26", 
            "start": "231.142"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "quantum mechanics.", 
            "dur": "2.25", 
            "start": "233.402"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, after all that, let&#39;s go back to the question,", 
            "dur": "2.947", 
            "start": "235.652"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;What is light?&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.476", 
            "start": "238.599"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, light isn&#39;t really like anything", 
            "dur": "2.398", 
            "start": "240.075"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we&#39;re used to dealing with in our everyday lives.", 
            "dur": "2.429", 
            "start": "242.473"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Sometimes it behaves like a particle", 
            "dur": "1.831", 
            "start": "244.902"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and other times it behaves like a wave,", 
            "dur": "2.286", 
            "start": "246.733"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but it isn&#39;t exactly like either.", 
            "dur": "2.711", 
            "start": "249.019"
        }
    ], 
